# semctl01: excluded — build-incompat, not a dd gap. Its test table uses
# unprototyped `void (*func_setup)()` fields but calls them with an argument;
# gcc-14 reads empty-paren as (void) and rejects "too many arguments", and no
# -fpermissive/-std flag rescues it (gnu89 then breaks the modern tst_safe
# headers it also pulls). Would need a source patch (out of scope for the lane).
# ipc     semctl      semctl/semctl01.c
ipc     semctl      semctl/semctl02.c
